text-indent:4.5pt'>&lt;b>&lt;span style='font-size:14.0pt'>THE VALUE OF THE GOLDEN
RULE&lt;/span>&lt;/b>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class=MsoNormal align=center style='margin-right:-.5in;text-align:center;
text-indent:4.5pt'>&lt;b>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt'>&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span>&lt;/b>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class=MsoNormal align=center style='margin-right:-.5in;text-align:center;
text-indent:4.5pt'>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt'>Virgil Warren, PhD&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class=MsoNormal style='margin-right:-.5in;text-align:justify;text-indent:
4.5pt;line-height:18.0pt'>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt'>&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class=MsoNormal style='margin-right:-.5in;text-align:justify;text-indent:
4.5pt;line-height:18.0pt'>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt'>  &lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class=MsoNormal style='margin-right:-.5in;text-align:justify;text-indent:
4.5pt;line-height:18.0pt'>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt'>                The
previous study on Matthew &lt;b>7&lt;/b>:12 dealt with the &lt;u>meaning&lt;/u> of the
Golden Rule. This study looks at the &lt;u>impact&lt;/u> of the Golden Rule on
individuals and on their relationships. In the parallel between &lt;i>“[Do] [to
others] [as you would have others do to you]”&lt;/i> and &lt;i>“[Love] [your
neighbor] [as yourself],” &lt;/i>we made two primary observations. (1) &lt;i>Do&lt;/i>
replaces &lt;i>love&lt;/i>; so love is an action that can be commanded. That doing is
a giving of ourselves for the joy of others. Often &lt;i>love&lt;/i> means giving of
ourselves for the needs of others, but we can also love God, who &lt;i>“is not
served by men’s hands as though he needed anything”&lt;/i> (Acts &lt;b>17&lt;/b>:25). It
is better, then, to define love broadly enough to include loving him. When we
meet people’s needs, we are increasing their happiness; so love becomes
self-giving for the joy of others.&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>BUILDING LIFE ON A FIRM FOUNDATION</title><link>https://christir.org/essays/interpretation/commentaries/sermon-on-the-mount-book/building-life-on-a-firm-foundation/</link><pubDate>Mon, 16 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/essays/interpretation/commentaries/sermon-on-the-mount-book/building-life-on-a-firm-foundation/</guid><description>&lt;style>
